                  <interp inst="t18311201-282-crimeloc1499" type="placeName" value="Brown's-lane, Spitalfields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-282-crimeloc1499" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-282-off1497 t18311201-282-crimeloc1499"></join>, and am a <rs id="t18311201-282-viclabel1500" type="occupation">trimming-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-282-victim2117 t18311201-282-viclabel1500"></join>. I have employed the prisoner between two and three years; he slept in the house on the 2nd of December - I had counted my money that night; I had one sovereign and five half-crowns in my watch-pocket, and one shilling and some halfpence in my trousers pocket, on a chair by the side of my bed - I awoke about half-past six o'clock; he was out of bed, and I heard the money rattle - I laid very still for a few minutes, and then I saw him go down on his knees, and replace the trousers on the chair; he left the room - I counted the money, and sent for a Policeman.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-282-person2119">
                  WILLIAM 
                  DRABBLE
               <interp inst="t18311201-282-person2119" type="surname" value="DRABBLE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-282-person2119" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-282-person2119" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-officer. I was sent for to the prosecutor's - I received the prisoner in charge, and found on him three 1d. pieces, a farthing, a knife, and a pair of scissors, but no half-crown.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-282-person2120">
                  WILLIAM 
                  WILLIAMSON
               <interp inst="t18311201-282-person2120" type="surname" value="WILLIAMSON"></interp>
